---
const faqs = [
  {
    question:
      'How many users can I invite to my organization and is there pricing change based on number of users?',
    answer:
      'There is no limit on number of users and there is no pricing change based on number of users. Pricing is flat $49/month irrepective of how many users are using the product.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Where can I find my billing data?',
    answer:
      'Click Account from dropdown menu in top right corner of your dashboard and you will find your billing data.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What is the refund policy?',
    answer:
      'We do not offer refund although you can cancel your subscription at any time. However, if you have any questions or concerns, please contact us at admin@quicklabs.in',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is data of my organization safe?',
    answer:
      'Yes, we are not sharing any of your data with someone else. Also, our interal teams have strict data security policies and we will not share your data with anyone.',
  },
  {
    question: "What kind of support I'll get if I have any questions?",
    answer:
      'You will do our best to answer your questions. If you have any questions or concerns, please contact us at admin@quicklabs.in anytime.',
  },
];
---

<div class='bg-white' id='faqs'>
  <div class='mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 lg:px-8'>
    <div class='mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-bold leading-10 tracking-tight text-gray-900'>
        Frequently asked questions
      </h2>
      <p class='mt-6 text-base leading-7 text-gray-600'>
        If you can’t find what you’re looking for, email our support team at
        <a
          href='mailto:admin@quicklabs.in'
          class='font-semibold text-slate-600 hover:text-indigo-600 hover:underline'
          >admin@quicklabs.in</a
        >. We will get back to you as soon as we can.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class='mt-20'>
      <dl
        class='space-y-12 sm:grid sm:grid-cols-2 sm:gap-x-6 sm:gap-y-12 sm:space-y-0 lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-x-10'
      >
        {
          faqs.map((faq) => {
            return (
              <div>
                <dt class='text-base font-semibold leading-7 text-gray-900'>
                  {faq.question}
                </dt>
                <dd class='mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-gray-600'>
                  {faq.answer}
                </dd>
              </div>
            );
          })
        }
      </dl>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
